Durban - Disaster management teams have been placed on high alert following as heavy rains continue to pour in parts of the province. KwaZulu-Natal MEC for Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (Cogta) Nomusa Dube-Ncube said teams are ready in preparation for the rains which are expected to continue until Wednesday. 

"The heavy rains which can cause localised flooding pose a serious risk to motorists and pedestrians. We therefore urge our disaster management teams to pay close attention to routes that are prone to flooding. We also urge motorists and pedestrians to exercise extreme caution,” she said.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Municipalities have been instructed to be on standby with emergency shelters should the need arise. KZN has suffered serious damage as a result of natural disasters, with houses swept away and lives lost when heavy rains devastated eThekwini last October.

On Monday, snow fell in some parts of the Eastern Cape. 

